"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"**1.)Which crypto is the most energy efficient and decentralized?**\\n\\n [$BTC](https://twitter.com/search?q=%24BTC&src=cashtag_click) (Bitcoin) [https://bitnodes.io](https://t.co/C4TDVVZIKQ) 14415 nodes Price per node $3.38 per node \\n\\n[$ETH](https://twitter.com/search?q=%24ETH&src=cashtag_click) (Ethereum) 5932 nodes [https://ethernodes.org/history](https://t.co/RFKvjZf7lu) $1.43 per node. \\n\\n[$XCH](https://twitter.com/search?q=%24XCH&src=cashtag_click) (CHIA) [https://chiaexplorer.com/charts/nodes](https://t.co/RsuJxMeJKP) 40963 nodes $0.002 per node\\n\\n**2.) Rig Electricity Usage per dollar spent.** \\n\\n$12k BTC asic rig uses around 3150w \\n\\n$10k Ethereum miner 1150w  \\n\\n$13k Chia miner + 32 disks 250w \\n\\n**3.) Now lets talk mining rig lifetime.** \\n\\nThe BTC Asic and Ethereum miners will no longer be power efficient after 3 or 4 years requiring you to repurchase them. \\n\\nThe Chia miner is just as good as the disks in it, with modern disks lasting 7-10 years.\\n\\n**4.) So, lets do a 7 year ROI on all three miners at current coin prices.** \\n\\n$12k BTC rig, 7 year profits after cost of the miners $12127.7 \\n\\n$10k ETH rig, 7 year profits after cost of the miner at 385mh/s $33,655 \\n\\n $13k Chia miner, 5216 plots. $19094.7 (estimated 2400$ 7 year electricity bill)\\n\\n**5.) what is the environmental cost of each of these miners?**\\n\\n [$BTC](https://twitter.com/search?q=%24BTC&src=cashtag_click), 130 metric tons of CO2 or 144095lbs of coal burnt \\n\\n [$ETH](https://twitter.com/search?q=%24ETH&src=cashtag_click), 50 metric tons of CO2 or 55236lbs of coal burnt\\n\\n [$XCH](https://twitter.com/search?q=%24XCH&src=cashtag_click), 10 metric tons of CO2, or 12008lbs of coal burnt \\n\\n \\n **6.) That's a lot of pollution for some internet money.** \\n\\nLets do a quick recap \\n\\nBTC, 7 year return $12127.7 and 130 metric tons of CO2 \\n\\nXCH, 7 year return $19094.7 and 10 metric tons of CO2 \\n\\nETH, 7 year return $33,655 and 50 metric tons of CO2 \\n\\nLet's look at what we learned form this \\n\\n \\n  [$BTC](https://twitter.com/search?q=%24BTC&src=cashtag_click) is dying, there is no avoiding it. It is too inefficient to survive the next decade with an inescapable energy crunch AND it is more profitable to mine other currencies.\\n\\n If you don't mind generating 5 times as much CO2 waste for 50% more profit on the gamble the you will be able to mine [$ETH](https://twitter.com/search?q=%24ETH&src=cashtag_click) for 7 years it is more profitable.\\n\\n [$XCH](https://twitter.com/search?q=%24XCH&src=cashtag_click) Chia really is the greenest of all the crypto currencies, the data here proves it beyond any doubt. If you care about DEFI and the environment this is the clear winner by any stretch of the imagination\\n\\nYou also forgot to mention a XCH miner will never go up in price. All BTC/ETH miners increased or held price for second hand market. Making a lot of the equipment recyclable. 5 year trend.  \\n \",\"timestamp\":1641897282,\"title\":\"Why $chia is the future of cryptoï¼Ÿ\"},\"digest\":\"MudbhgKRqBoCVvrcK64l7zZkFLnrKXaon64KnuuMtTY\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x2b59e06DB4d463f20Cec5A603Ee7D2d5179D2bEe\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"y2qhTv-OfpEfgPL_25w1D5DdC7beT1KNQxrvkKclOuo\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"BYjUvaIkvVX0Z-cyj2pHOo0MDF3JZINyUgQoFN0EGGQ\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"FjssIzih8EeSMUImgsHrEz5ztqLXBOEH-rIQH-Gzn43wU8DeEvO_cQfVerq1JXSzPmMiqlD0AsYXSuRhcvg9Qw\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x4a7a05ccbb6a1b1fd4f311b4f57b118274fb8aec4338d2be48eec9c9597c17767dab5ccbe3ce3e98d1472138523b5bc58dabf71a88f1576b94c9aa1bf5828a621c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"y2qhTv-OfpEfgPL_25w1D5DdC7beT1KNQxrvkKclOuo\